This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Motion hearing on December 7, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Preliminary hearing on December 7, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Defendant enters a plea of NOT GUILTY to all counts.

1:37 PM DA calls case and states appearances. Defendant Storm W. Waltenberg appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Christopher Michael Restemayer in court for Storm W. Waltenberg.  Attorney Karl J. Kelz in court for State of Wisconsin. Court questions defendant on being personally present. Defendant freely, voluntarily, and intelligently waives his right to be personally present in the courtroom. DA Kelz calls witness: Officer Luke Larson with the Park Falls Police Department. Witness sworn. Direct questioning of the witness by DA Kelz. Witness identifies the defendant on record. Cross examination by Attorney Restemayer. witness excused.  DA Kelz calls witness: Officer Dominick Koller with the Park Falls Police Department. Witness sworn. Direct questioning of the witness by DA Kelz. witness excused. Statement by DA Kelz. Statement by Attorney Restemayer. Court finds probable cause exists that a crime was committed and binds DE over for trial. Information filed, acknowledged by parties and reading waived. Proceed to arraignment.
Preliminary hearing on August 24, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant may not have contact with the individual(s): S.V.O.R      DOB: 11/21/1992
**No Contact includes: Going to or remaining in any place the individual resides, is employed at, attends school at, or any public location the individual is temporarily located. Contact through means of telephone. Electronic devices, Social media, email, regular mail, or a 3rd party individual is prohibited. The only exception to this order is contact through your attorney or law enforcement in appropriate circumstances.

10:09 AM Defendant Storm W. Waltenberg appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Karl J. Kelz in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Nicholas Smith appeared for Attorney Christopher Michael Restemayer. Complaint acknowledged, reading waived. Preliminary Hearing requested, time limits not waived. DA Kelz gives bond recommendations. Bond ordered as requested by the State.
